title: Dental Implants: More Than a Screw, a Complete Solution
cate_info_ai: [{"catId":611295,"catPath":"Medicine and health => Medical Devices => Implants => Dental Implants","catUrl":"https://vtyler.alibaba.com/vtyler/index.htm?categoryId=611295"}]
description:
Dental Implants: More Than a Screw, a Complete Solution 
 What is a Dental Implant? 
 A dental implant is a small titanium screw placed in the jawbone to replace the root of a missing tooth. Over time, the bone bonds naturally to the screw in a process called osseointegration. This makes the implant very firm and secure. Two other parts are placed on top of the implant: a connector (called an abutment) and a crown, which is the visible surface that mimics the tooth. Implants are made of safe and durable materials, designed to last for many years and withstand the force of chewing. 
 Different Types of Prostheses 
 There are different types of implant-supported prostheses. Removable prostheses, which can be removed and replaced, are a more economical option. They are made of resin and are supported by several implants. They can be removed for cleaning. They are comfortable, but not as comfortable as a fixed prosthesis. Fixed prostheses are glued or screwed to the implant, and only the dentist can remove them. They are used for both individual teeth and for full-mouth restorations. They are made of ceramic or zirconium, highly aesthetic and durable materials. They are the closest option to having natural teeth. 
 Conclusion 
 A good implant treatment depends not only on the surgery itself, but also on a good prosthesis. That's why it's so important to work with experienced professionals and work with quality materials.
